# Topic ACLs.
#
# Drivers authenticate with their driverId as the MQTT username, so the
# %u pattern locks each driver to their own publish topic — a compromised
# client can't publish as another driver or snoop the fleet.

# The bridge service fans locations out and needs full access.
user bridge
topic readwrite #

# Each driver may only publish their own location.
pattern write drivers/%u/location

# Rider apps share a read-only account scoped to trip channels. They never
# see raw drivers/# topics — the bridge re-publishes per-trip, so a rider
# only learns the position of the driver assigned to *their* trip.
user rider
topic read trips/#
